title: Eddie "Lockjaw" Davis - The Complete Coookbook Session
description:
EDDIE "LOCKJAW" DAVIS with SHIRLEY SCOTT - THE COMPLETE COOKBOOK SESSIONS

This release presents the complete Cookbook session by Eddie "Lockjaw" Davis in a quartet/quintet format with Shirley Scott on organ and, on some tracks, Jerome Richardson on flute, as well as tenor and baritone sax. This is the first time that all of this material is containred on a single set and in the order in which it was recorded. This set included the complete contents of the original LPs THE EDDIE "LOCKJAW" DAVIS COOKBOOKS (Vols. 1 to 3; Prestige 7141, 7161 & 7212), JAWS (Prestige 7134) & SMOKIN' (Prestige 7301), plus all of the other songs from the same sessions and a quartet set by the exact same personnel (but with Scott on piano instead of organ) added as a bonus.

Eddie "Lockjaw" Davis - tenor sax
Jerome Richardson - flute, tenor & baritone sax
Shirley Scott - organ
George Duvivier - bass
Arthur Edgehill - drums

Jerome Richardson out on CD One, 1 & 7-13, and on CD Two, 1-9.

Hackensack, New Jersey, June 20 (CD One, 1-6), 
September 12, (CD One, 7-13 & CD Two, 1-9)
& December 5 (CD Two 10-14 & CD Three, 1-7),
1958.

BONUS TRACKS
(CD Two, 15 & CD Three, 8-13):
Same personnel except Shirley Scott switches
to piano and Richardson is omitted.
Englewood Cliffs, New Jersey,
January 31, 1960.

Includes 24-page booklet with complete information, and original liner notes and artwork.

2010 Solar Records
